From May 19, 2016 through June 30, 2016, 19 patients with hPIV-3, including eight HCT recipients and one healthcare worker, were identified in haematology ward B (Figure 1
). Table I
shows the clinical characteristics of these patients. The mean age of the patients was 44 years. The majority of the patients were lymphopenic (12; 64%). Six of the eight HCT recipients had undergone transplantation <12 months before hPIV-3 infection developed. Of the 19 infected patients, four had upper and 12 had lower respiratory tract infections, and five (26%) died of hPIV-3 infection. Of the 19 patients, six (32%) were community-onset infection (symptom onset within <7 days of hospitalization) and 13 (68%) were hospital-onset infection (symptom onset within ≥7 days of hospitalization). Fourteen patients (74%) had other serious concurrent infections, including invasive fungal infections (eight patients). Median length (interquartile range) of viral shedding from respiratory specimen was 18 days (14–19 days).
